#Text=Dolor Davis
#Text=Dolor Davis was born 1593 , in Benefield , Northamptonshire , England .
#Text=He married Margery Willard daughter of Richard Willard of Horsemonden , yeomen in Parish church , East Farleigh , Kent , England March 29th , 1624 .
#Text=Margery was baptized at Horsemonden , November 7th 1602 and died before 1667 .
#Text=Margery 's brother Simon would become a lifelong friend of Dolor Davis .
#Text=Other than being a carpenter and Master Builder nothing is known of him until he sailed to America and landed in Boston in May 1634 .
#Text=He quickly bought 25 acres ( 10ha ) of land on the west side of the river in Cambridge , Massachusettson August 4,1635 . [ 1 ] [ about where Harvard College is today ]
#Text=On April 17 , 1635 , his wife and three children embarked from London for New England , arrived on the Elizabeth , and they decided to live in Cambridge .
#Text=On June 4 , 1635 , Davis bought a lot of half a rood for a home , which was located on what is now the corner of Winthrop and Dunster streets . [ 2 ]
#Text=However , Davis and his friend Willard decided not to stay in Cambridge , like many of the settlers during the years of 1635-1636 .
#Text=In August 1635 , Davis and Willard sold their land in Cambridge to Richard Girling . [ 2 ] and became a member of the Duxbury Church in 1640 as well . [ 3 ]
#Text=Duxbury
#Text=Dolor Davis moved to Duxbury , August 5 , 1638-39 , was admitted freemen , and was granted land there in 1640 .
#Text=During the year of 1640 , Davis was granted 50 acres ( 20ha ) and land for his cows to graze .
#Text=He became a member of the Duxbury Church in 1640 as well . [ 4 ]
#Text=Dolor and his wife were dismissed from the Duxbury church to the Barnstable church , August 27th 1648 .
#Text=He only stayed here for 3 years before he moved to Barnstable
#Text=Barnstable
#Text=In 1643 , Davis moved again , this time to Barnstable .

#Text=He and his sons appeared on a list of men in Barnstable between " 16 to 60 years of age to bear arms " . [ 5 ] In June 1645 , he was sworn in as a member of the Grand Inquest of Plymouth Colony .
#Text=He also tried to become a freeman , and a year later he became a freeman of Barnstable . [ 6 ]
#Text=In 1652 , Dolor Davis was chosen as a surveyor of highways in Barnstable .
#Text=In 1654 , he was then chosen to become the constable of Barnstable . [ 7 ]
#Text=He continued to live in Barnstable and practice his trade as a carpenter until he left for Concord in 1655 .
#Text=In 1666 Dollar returned to Barnstable From Concord and remained in Barnstable till he died during June 1673 .
#Text=Dolor 's will , dated September 13th 1672 , was proved July 2 , 1673 .
#Text=Dolor mentions his sons Simon and Samuel as already having their portions ; his son John and son in law Lewis , with Mary , Lewis 's wife ; daughter Ruth Hall .
#Text=Concord
#Text=In 1656 Dolor left Plymouth Colony and returned to Concord , Massachusetts , his home for the next 11 years .
#Text=He bought 150 acres ( 61ha ) of land , with a house in an assortment of different parcels , from Roger Draper of Concord . [ 8 ]
#Text=This property soon became Davis 's homestead in Concord .
#Text=He also met up with his friend Simon Willard while he lived in Concord .
#Text=In 1659 , he was recorded as one of the landowners in Concord .
#Text=Sometime during his stay in Concord , his wife Margery died .
#Text=Alone , he left Concord in 1666 back to Barnstable .
#Text=Pronunciation of his first name
#Text=Dolor Davis 's name is pronounced dollar .
#Text=Throughout his life , the variations of his name are spelt Dolor , Dolar , Dolard , Dolord , Dolore , Dollard , Dolerd , Dollerd , Dollar and Dollar .
#Text=Marriage and children
#Text=Dolar Davis married Margery Willard of Horsemonden , Kent , in 1624 .
#Text=Margery Willard was born sometime around 1602 , as that is when she was christened .
#Text=They had six children , three who were born in England and the other three born in America .
#Text=They were :
#Text=John , born 1626 , in East Farleigh , England , inherited homestead ; Died April 9th 1703 in Banestable , MA . ; married Hannah Linnell
#Text=Mary , born 1631 , England
#Text=Elizabeth , born 1633 , England , died young
#Text=Samuel , born July 11th 1639 , Cambridge , Massachusetts ; Died October 30 , 1720 in Concord , Middlesex Co. MA . ; married
#Text=Mary Meadows
#Text=Simon , born 1640 , Massachusetts
#Text=Ruth , born 1645 , Barnstable , Massachusetts
